SIMPLE: insufficiency
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insufficiency
<hw>In`suf*fi"cien*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>insufficientia</ets>: cf. F. <ets>insuffisance</ets>, whence OE.
<ets>insuffisance</ets>. See <er>Insufficient</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being insufficient; lack of
sufficiency; deficiency; inadequateness; <as>as, the
<ex>insufficiency</ex> of provisions, of an excuse, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>insufficiency</qex> of the light of nature is, by the
light of Scripture, . . . fully supplied.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lack of power or skill; inability; incapacity;
incompetency; <as>as, the <ex>insufficiency</ex> of a man for an
office</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insufficient</ent>⟦br⟧
